      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:3:40:6",
      "text": [
        " مَنْ أَحَبَّ أَنْ يَمْشِيَ مَمْشَى الْكِرَامِ الْكَاتِبِينَ فَلْيَمْشِ بِجَنْبَيِ السَّرِيرِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Abu Al Al Ashary, from Muhammad Bin Abdul Jabbar, from Al Hajjal, from Ali Bin Shajara, from Abu Al Wafa’a Al Murady, from Sadeyr, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who loves to walk the walk of the Honourable Recorders (Angels), so let him walk by the side of the coffin’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. Abu Ali al-Ash’ariy has narrated from Muhammad ibn ‘Abd al-Jabbar from al-Hajjal from Ali ibn Shajarah from abu al-Wafa’ al- Muradiy from Sadir who has said the following: “Abu Ja‘far, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘If one wants to walk (in a funeral procession) like the honorable angels, then walk on either side of the coffin.’” "
        ]
      }
